	<section class="about dark-theme">
		<div class="about-content">
		  <h2>About Sports</h2>
		  <p>Sport encompasses a wide range of competitive physical activities and games aimed at using, maintaining, or improving physical abilities. It is a universal language that brings people together, fostering unity, sportsmanship, and discipline. Whether played for leisure or at a professional level, sports are integral to a healthy lifestyle.</p>
		  
		  <p>Participating in sports offers numerous physical and mental health benefits, such as enhancing cardiovascular fitness, improving muscle strength, boosting mood, and reducing stress. Additionally, sports can foster confidence, build leadership skills, and promote teamwork.</p>
		  
		  <h3>Popular Types of Sports</h3>
		  <ul>
			<li><strong>Team Sports:</strong> These include games like soccer, basketball, and cricket, where players work together to achieve a common goal. Team sports are excellent for building communication and teamwork skills.</li>
			<li><strong>Individual Sports:</strong> Sports such as tennis, swimming, and athletics focus on personal performance, helping individuals develop self-discipline and perseverance.</li>
			<li><strong>Adventure Sports:</strong> Activities like rock climbing, surfing, and skiing are ideal for thrill-seekers. These sports often require specialized skills and promote confidence and resilience.</li>
			<li><strong>Precision Sports:</strong> Archery, shooting, and golf require high levels of concentration and accuracy, making them perfect for honing focus and patience.</li>
		  </ul>
		  
		  <h3>Benefits of Engaging in Sports</h3>
		  <p>Engaging in sports regularly contributes to personal development in several ways:</p>
		  <ul>
			<li><strong>Physical Health:</strong> Sports improve fitness, reduce the risk of chronic diseases, and promote an active lifestyle.</li>
			<li><strong>Mental Well-being:</strong> Sports can help combat anxiety and depression, boosting overall mental health through physical activity and social interactions.</li>
			<li><strong>Social Skills:</strong> Through team-based sports, individuals learn valuable communication and collaboration skills, building lasting friendships and networks.</li>
			<li><strong>Character Building:</strong> Sports encourage values like discipline, resilience, and a positive attitude towards success and failure.</li>
		  </ul>
		  
		  <a href="exploregames.html" class="btn">Explore More Games</a>
		</div>
		
		<div class="about-image">
		  <img src="olympic.png" alt="Olympic Games Image">
		</div>
	  </section>
	  
</head>
